Locals and tourists enjoy in the Pari Mahal Garden which is situated on the Zabarwan mountain Range, near Cheshmashahi in Srinagar. Pari Mahal or The Angels' Abode is a seven terraced garden located at the top of Zabarwan mountain range over-looking city of Srinagar and south-west of Dal Lake. The architecture depicts an example of Islamic architecture and patronage of art during the reign of the then Mughal Emperor Shah Jahan. The garden was built by the Mughal Prince Dara Shikoh in the mid-1600s.
